{"title":"2022 Orange Crush Pro Hardtail gets tougher w/ new more progressive geometry","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/19/2022-orange-crush-pro-hardtail-gets-tougher-w-new-more-progressive-geometry/","date":1634637650000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-800x500.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush pro 29&quot; hardtail mountain bike aluminium frame red\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-800x500.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-297x186.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-120x75.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-768x480.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-1536x960.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-274822\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Orange Bikes has revamped their original hardcore hardtail to deliver, yet again, longer, slacker geometry, improving the strength of the frameset along the way. The 27.5″ model, 29″ model and MX are updated with a new one-piece chainstay yoke forged for enhanced strength to improve the frame’s lateral rigidity. Let’s get into it.</p><h2>2022 Orange Crush Pro</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush pro models red sand colorways\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114613/2022-orange-crush-pro-models-sand-red-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 2022 Orange Crush sees a steeper seat tube of 75.5°, bringing the rider further forward for a more direct pedaling position. Improving the pedaling efficiency was a priority for Orange; not only have they redesigned the geometry around that significantly steeper seat angle, but the chainstay yoke redesign, aimed at improving overall strength, also improved the rear end’s rigidity to make that power transfer from the drivetrain more efficient.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush bb chainstay yoke\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120313/2022-orange-crush-hardtail-mtb-chainstay-yoke-logo-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>To further improve the frame’s robustness, the Crush now sees a tapered headtube to increase the size of the weld areas for the top tube and down tube. Orange are sticking with the 73mm BB shell for the strength benefits, plus the 148mm rear end.</p><div id=\"attachment_275269\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275269\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush 29er headtube taper\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1065\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/19044348/2022-orange-crush-29er-1536x1022.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275269\">Cable grommets are now CNC machined; routing for the dropper post is internal with external routing for the rear brake hose and gear cable</p></div><p>Both the 27.5″ and 29er versions slacken off at the head tube, with head angles of 63.5° and 64.5°, respectively. Reach elongates, yet again; the large frames now boast a reach of 480mm. Those changes are coupled with a switch to reduced offset forks (37mm in 27.5″ and 44mm in 29″) and 42.5mm reach stem in an attempt to keep the rider’s weight forward enough to prevent front end wash out.</p><div id=\"attachment_275065\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275065\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush tire clearance\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120316/2022-orange-crush-seat-stay-join-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275065\">A new gusset at the seat stay-seat tube interface adds strength in this area</p></div><p>Chainstay length remains unchanged at 445mm on the 29er and 430mm on the 27.5″. Tire clearance is unaffected by the changes to the chainstay yoke, still plentiful with a max of 2.6″ on the 27.5″ and 2.5″ on the 29er.</p><div id=\"attachment_275060\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275060\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes.jpg\" alt=\"orange crush pro 29er hardtail mtb sand color\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes-297x186.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes-800x500.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes-120x75.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes-768x480.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114616/Crush-Pro-2022-orange-bikes-1536x960.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275060\">The 2022 Orange Crush Pro 27.5″ Hardcore Hardtail in Sandy Playa</p></div><div id=\"attachment_275068\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275068\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"2022 ornage crush pro 27.5&quot; geometry chart\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1337\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart-297x248.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart-800x669.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart-120x100.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart-768x642.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120805/2022-orange-crush-pro-275-geometry-chart-1536x1284.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275068\">The 27.5″ version is available in sizes S-XL</p></div><div id=\"attachment_275058\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275058\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush pro 29&quot; hardtail mountain bike aluminium frame red\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-297x186.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-800x500.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-120x75.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-768x480.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15114610/2022-orange-Crush_29_Pro-2022-SO-Sliced%400.5x-1536x960.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275058\">The 2022 Orange Crush Pro 29″ Hardcore Hardtail in Candy Red</p></div><div id=\"attachment_275067\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275067\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange crush pro 29er geometry chart\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1651\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart-291x300.jpg 291w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart-800x826.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart-116x120.jpg 116w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart-768x792.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/15120801/2022-orange-crush-pro-29-geometry-chart-1489x1536.jpg 1489w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275067\">The 29er is available in sizes M-XL</p></div><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The 2022 Orange Crush is available now in the Pro model only, retailing at £2600 for both wheel size options. That cash gets you a RockShox Lyrik Select fork (140mm travel on the 29er, 150mm travel on the 27.5″), a SRAM SX Eagle drivetrain, SRAM Guide T brakes and Maxxis Minion DHF tires with EXO casing on WTB rims.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.orangebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>OrangeBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e2d4997fe457585ad1eb330e7867269cd5d0e3084cae3764a59905cb5b957009","category":"Cycling"}